passages.text: August 31, 2025 06:30 PM GMT

Update on orders: If the new NVIDIA chipset is delivered in 1H26, given a 6-month construction period, we think GDS would likely see relevant DC orders in 4Q25. The company noted that they are seeing some decent demand from traditional CPU businesses, including food delivery, which saw some expansion from key customers. Those orders mostly use existing inventories and require limited incremental capex.

Outlook: Even without a major breakthrough in NVIDIA chipset supply, GDS believes it could still win orders backed by domestic GPUs and traditional workload. It continues to believe it could deliver 200- 300MW annual capacity in the future with \(\sim\) Rmb5bn capex per year.

Supply/demand dynamics: GDS sees its project IRR increasing by 1ppt due to faster unitization ramp- up. It also noted that window guidance from the government has been restricting incremental supply to the market. If this is sustained, the company thinks the industry would likely see better pricing in the future.
